OSX Global Hotkeys
==================

## Keyboar navigation
^ F1			Tooogle keyboard navigation
^ F2			Move foucs to menubar
^ F3			Move foucs to the dock
^ F8			Move foucs to menubar tiems (Not working?)
^ F4			Move foucs to active or next window
^ F6			Move foucs to floating window
Cmd Option `	Move foucs to window drawer

Cmd Opt D		Toggle dock hiding


## Screen capture
Cmd Shift 3		Capture entire screen and save to file
Cmd Shift 4		Capture from cropped screen
Cmd Shift 5		Capture current window
^ Cmd Shift 3	Capture entire screen to clipboard
^ Cmd Shift 4	Capture from cropped screen to clipboard


## IME
^ Space			Next input source
^ Option Space  Prev input source
^ Shift Space	Show/Hide trackpad handwriting


## Finder
Cmd Shft F		Recent files (Spotlight)

## Mission Control
^ Cmd ↑			Mission Control
^ Cmd ↓			Application Windows
F11				Show Desktop
^ Cmd ←/→		Move left/right a space

## TickTick
^ Shift A		Show Quick Add bar (User Defined)
^ Cmd O			Show/Hide Mini Window

## Yoink
F5				Toggle Yoink
^ Cmd Opt X		Add selected files to Yoink
^ Cmd Opt Y		Add selected text to Yoink


## Shiori
^ Opt F12		Find					(User Defined)

## Bartender		
^ F12    		Show hidden items		(User Defined)
^ F11    		Show full menu bar		(User Defined)

## Clipto
^ Shift E    	Show/Hide app					(User Defined)
^ Shift P    	Toggle clipboard monitoring		(User Defined)



## ⌘ ⌥ ⇧ ⇥ ↩ ↑ ↓ ← → ##








